results.name: Swap twin prime pairs of form (4*k+3,4*(k+1)+1) in prime factorization of n.
comment: a(a(n))=n, a self-inverse permutation of natural numbers.
link: Index entries for sequences that are permutations of the natural numbers
formula: Multiplicative with a(p) = (if p mod 4 = 3 and p+2 is prime then p+2 else (if p mod 4 = 1 and p-2 is prime then p-2 else p)), p prime.
results.author: _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Jun 07 2002
